{
  "stem": "26142.6",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They used to call him, you know, a nickname, [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Yovichka ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know, a funny thing, he must have had some whisky somewhere because it was [LAUGHS] emanating from him all the time.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know in the house.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was a terribly nervous person.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "His wife would go out and she would buy, already that time you could buy carrots, you could buy tomatoes, you could buy corn on the cob, you know, and they would bring.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we went out also to buy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If you could find Hungarian soldiers, we could buy cigarettes and for cigarettes you could-- anyway, a funny thing happened.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This guy was always hungry.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he used to walk around and we had to have a laugh in all this [INAUDIBLE] and he spoke to him in Yiddish and he was talking like he talks to his stomach.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He would say, [YIDDISH], which translates in English, he says, stomach, stomach, don't bother me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Do I have it and I don't give it to you?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And that made us really laugh but he was-- he was drunk.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was drinking.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And another thing which was, I have no-- I don't know how and why, a Ukrainian priest would come in every day.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Even he had an eye on that widow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he would visit her but he would come every day into the house.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were there for a few days, like I said, 10, 12 days.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my sister-in-law, she would talk to him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Of course, we spoke Ukrainian, all of us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she would talk to him, and she asked him to-- to write us a letter, to give us a letter to whom it may concern, that to please, we are Hungarian from the Carpathian refugees.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
